            <div class="lesson-content-memo">Effective Field</div>

           <!-- LHS -->
           <div class="col-md-9 col-lg-9">
In general, the spins precess about the the effective magnetic field, $B_{eff}$.
This is a vector combination of a $B_0$ and a $B_1$ component.
The $B_0$ component will represent off-resonance.
So if we are in a rotating frame which is not quite on-resonance, then the spins
will precess about the direction of $B_{eff}$, which may be at some angle in between horizontal and vertical.
